TY  - JOUR
T1  - Persuasion with Multiple Actions
AU  - Khantadze, Davit
AU  - Kremer, Ilan
AU  - Skrzypacz, Andrzej
Y1  - 2024/11/22
PY  - 2024
DA  - 2025/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/734125
DO  - 10.1086/734125
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 1497
EP  - 1526
VL  - 133
IS  - 5
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - We consider a Bayesian persuasion model in which multiple receivers take one action each. We compare simultaneous procedures with sequential ones. In a simultaneous procedure, all the receivers act simultaneously following the realization of a single public signal. In a sequential procedure, receivers receive information and take actions sequentially. We characterize the conditions under which the optimal sequential procedure leads to a higher payoff and characterize the optimal ordering of actions.
AB  - We consider a Bayesian persuasion model in which multiple receivers take one action each. We compare simultaneous procedures with sequential ones. In a simultaneous procedure, all the receivers act simultaneously following the realization of a single public signal. In a sequential procedure, receivers receive information and take actions sequentially. We characterize the conditions under which the optimal sequential procedure leads to a higher payoff and characterize the optimal ordering of actions.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/734125
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/734125
Y2  - 2026/04/24
